title: Sources
text:
The data from this project were pulled from the US census bureau. To clean the data, many changes were made to the formatting in order to make it more readable for R. Information on the type of Visa given out was omitted. The data is stored in its own directory in the project.
The data contains more than 2000 lines on different immigration visas across almost 200 countries. The immigration statistics were fitted in order to make a model and a few values were dropped due to having no data. Generative AI assisted in the creation of this project. All data and data fitting was done by humans.

title: Immigration
text: The following data were extracted from the US Census Bureau which detailed Visas that were given out and the country of origin of the person to which the Visa was given. The data were then fitted into a gaussian model to allow for predictions based on the country of origin of any given person. Each country had different amounts of Visas given out which affected their probability value. Finally a plot was made with the fitted model that is displayed here. I modeled an probability variable, a function of the origin of the person asking for the Visa. Mexico Is far and away the highest acceptor of US visas out of every country in the world.
